.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-DELETE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-delete \- Delete live dashboards by UID or folder path.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard delete [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete live dashboards by UID or folder path.
.PP
Use this when you need to remove one dashboard, a folder subtree, or a subtree plus the matched folders themselves.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-uid
delete one dashboard by UID.
.TP
.B \-\-path
delete dashboards under one folder subtree.
.TP
.B \-\-delete\-folders
with \-\-path, also remove matched folders.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
acknowledge the live delete.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
preview and confirm interactively.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run, \-\-table, \-\-json, \-\-output\-format, \-\-no\-header
preview output controls.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Delete live dashboards by UID or folder path.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard delete --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --uid cpu-main --dry-run --json
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
